The Supreme Court decision in Students for Fair Admissions v. Harvard and Students for Fair Admissions v. University of North Carolina is seen as a setback for the nation. It overturns established precedent and makes it harder for students from underrepresented backgrounds to access opportunities that can help them reach their full potential. The ruling will reduce diversity in schools, which is believed to benefit all students by providing opportunities to learn from people with different backgrounds. This decision will have long-lasting effects on the education and leadership of future generations. In response, it is important to prioritize ensuring that all young people have the chance to succeed.